items.title: SBI Life net profit dips 7% in Q2 on higher expenses
items.description: SBI Life Insurance experienced a 7% decrease in net profit during the second quarter of FY26, largely because of rising costs. Nevertheless, there's a silver lining as the Annualised Premium Equivalent surged by 10%.

items.title: Zen Technologies Q2 Results: Cons PAT slips 2% to Rs 62 crore, revenue tumbles 28%
items.description: Zen Technologies reported a 28% fall in Q2 FY26 revenue to Rs 173.5 crore, while net profit dipped 2.2% to Rs 62 crore. H1FY26 shows a 30% revenue decline and 20% lower profit.

items.title: Kotak Mahindra Bank Q2 Results: Net profit falls 3% to Rs 3,253 crore, NII up 4% at Rs 7,311 crore
items.description: Kotak Mahindra Bank Q2 Results: Kotak Mahindra Bank on Saturday, October 25, reported a 2.7% year-on-year decline in its standalone net profit for the September quarter at Rs 3,253 crore, compared to Rs 3,344 crore in the year ago period.
